    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS - MAINTENANCE - RETIGHTENING SPRING U-BOLT NUTS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
        <title>RETIGHTENING SPRING U-BOLT NUTS</title>
        <para>For both new vehicles and for those having suspension spring service, retighten the spring U-bolt nuts
            after the vehicle has operated under load for 1,000 miles (1,600 kilometers) or six months, whichever comes
            first.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
